# Frontend (`fe/`)

- **Stack**: Vite, React, TypeScript. Package root is `fe/` (see `fe/package.json`).
- Prefer existing UI patterns: **Headless UI** plus shared primitives under `fe/src/components/ui/` (Tailwind; class patterns often mirror shadcn-style naming). Use project scripts (`npm run dev`, `npm run full-check` from `fe/`). See [ADR 0002](../../adr/0002-frontend-ui-stack.md) for the UI stack summary.

## UI language

All **user-visible** strings in the app MUST be **Spanish (es-AR)**. File names, routes, types, and props remain **English** (see workspace rule _English file and path names_). Use `es-AR` (or neutral Spanish consistent with the app) for `toLocaleString` / dates when formatting values shown to users.

## Mobile-first (default)

Treat **narrow / touch** layouts as the baseline; widen and add complexity only at larger breakpoints.

- **CSS / Tailwind**: Unprefixed classes are the mobile default. Use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` (and up) to _add_ or _change_ behavior for larger viewports — never assume desktop-first and strip down with `max-*` unless there is a strong reason.
- **Layout**: Stack and scroll on small screens first; side-by-side, sidebars, and dense grids are enhancements at `sm` / `md` / `lg` as the rest of the app does.
- **Interaction**: Prefer tap-friendly targets and spacing on the base styles; denser layouts and hover affordances can layer on larger breakpoints.
- When unsure, **design and implement the smallest viewport first**, then scale up.

## PWA and service worker updates

- **Default:** `vite-plugin-pwa` uses **`registerType: 'prompt'`** with **`injectRegister: false`** and React **`useRegisterSW`** from `virtual:pwa-register/react`. The UI lives in [`fe/src/components/PwaUpdateBanner.tsx`](fe/src/components/PwaUpdateBanner.tsx): a **fixed bottom bar** (not a modal), **safe-area** padding, and **large tap targets** (`min-h-11`). Users reload only when they tap **Actualizar**; **Más tarde** dismisses until the next update check.
- **User-visible copy** for update flows MUST stay **Spanish (es-AR)**. Do not switch this banner to English for developer convenience.
- **When to use `autoUpdate` instead:** only if product explicitly prefers silent activation and accepts possible surprise reloads; document the change in [`work-files/adr/0001-pwa-update-strategy.md`](work-files/adr/0001-pwa-update-strategy.md) and adjust the banner/registration code.
- **True “force upgrade”** (e.g. breaking API) is **not** handled by the service worker alone: use an app-level minimum client/API version and a **blocking** screen if needed; keep that separate from the PWA refresh bar unless you intentionally merge the flows.
- **Icons:** Web app manifest and `apple-touch-icon` use **PNG** sizes derived from [`fe/public/pwa-icon.svg`](fe/public/pwa-icon.svg) (`pwa-192.png`, `pwa-512.png`, `apple-touch-icon.png`). Regenerate PNGs from the SVG if the mark changes; re-check **Add to Home Screen** on iOS and Android after visual changes.
